6 Section 3. Section 87-6-601, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "87-6-601. Trapping and snaring offenses. (1) A person may not use a trap or snare for the
8 purpose of trapping or snaring a fur-bearing animal, a predatory animal, or a nongame species unless:
9 (a) the trap or snare is tagged with a metal tag bearing an individual identifying number issued by
10 the department or the owner's name and address unless the person is trapping or snaring on the person's land
11 or an irrigation ditch right-of-way contiguous to the person's land; and
12 (b) the trap or snare is set in a manner, including in accordance with any setback requirement
13 established pursuant to [section 1], and at a time so that it will not unduly endanger livestock. A person who
14 injures livestock in a trap or snare is liable for damages to the owner of the livestock.
15 (2) A person may not use a trap or snare for the purpose of trapping or snaring a fur-bearing
16 animal, a predatory animal, or a nongame species on private property without obtaining permission from the
17 landowner, the lessee, or their agents.
18 (3) A person may not at any time willfully destroy, open or leave open, or partially destroy a house
19 of any muskrat or beaver, except that trapping in the house of muskrats is not prohibited when authorized by
20 the commission.
21 (4) A person shall set a trap in accordance with any setback requirement established pursuant to
22 [section 1].
23 (4)(5) (a) A person may not destroy, disturb, or remove any trap or snare belonging to another person
24 or remove wildlife from a trap or snare belonging to another person without permission of the owner of the trap
25 or snare, except that from March 1 to October 1 of each year a person may remove any snare from land owned
26 or leased by the person if the snare would endanger livestock.
27 (b) This subsection (4) (5) does not apply to a law enforcement officer acting within the scope of
28 the officer's duty.
